#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.30"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.30:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.30:0.2"
msgid "3. Puggalavagga "
msgstr "3. Persons "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.30:0.3"
msgid "30. Avakujjasutta "
msgstr "30. Upside-down "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.30:1.1"
msgid "“Tayome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“These three kinds of people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.2"
msgid "Katame tayo? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.3"
msgid "Avakujjapañño puggalo, ucchaṅgapañño puggalo, puthupañño puggalo. "
msgstr "One with upside-down wisdom, one with wisdom on their lap, and one with wide wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.30:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, avakujjapañño puggalo? "
msgstr "And who is the person with upside-down wisdom? "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ārāmaṃ gantā hoti abhikkhaṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ santike dhammassavanāya. "
msgstr "It’s someone who often goes to the monastery to hear the teaching in the presence of the mendicants. "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.6"
msgid "Tassa bhikkhū dhammaṃ desenti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsenti. "
msgstr "The mendicants teach them Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And they reveal a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.7"
msgid "So tasmiṃ āsane nisinno tassā kathāya neva ādiṃ manasi karoti, na majjhaṃ manasi karoti, na pariyosānaṃ manasi karoti; "
msgstr "But even while sitting there, that person doesn’t pay attention to the beginning, middle, or end of the discussion. "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.8"
msgid "vuṭṭhitopi tamhā āsanā tassā kathāya neva ādiṃ manasi karoti, na majjhaṃ manasi karoti, na pariyosānaṃ manasi karoti. "
msgstr "And when they get up from their seat, they don’t pay attention to the beginning, middle, or end of the discussion. "

#. VAR: nikujjo → nikkujjo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.30:1.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kumbho nikujjo tatra udakaṃ āsittaṃ vivaṭṭati, no saṇṭhāti; "
msgstr "It’s like when a pot full of water is tipped over, so the water drains out and doesn’t stay. "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.10"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo ārāmaṃ gantā hoti abhikkhaṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ santike dhammassavanāya. "
msgstr "In the same way, someone often goes to the monastery to hear the teaching in the presence of the mendicants. "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.11"
msgid "Tassa bhikkhū dhammaṃ desenti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsenti. "
msgstr "The mendicants teach them Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And they reveal a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.12"
msgid "So tasmiṃ āsane nisinno tassā kathāya neva ādiṃ manasi karoti, na majjhaṃ manasi karoti, na pariyosānaṃ manasi karoti; "
msgstr "But even while sitting there, that person doesn’t pay attention to the discussion in the beginning, middle, or end. "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.13"
msgid "vuṭṭhitopi tamhā āsanā tassā kathāya neva ādiṃ manasi karoti, na majjhaṃ manasi karoti, na pariyosānaṃ manasi karoti. "
msgstr "And when they get up from their seat, they don’t pay attention to the beginning, middle, or end of the discussion. "

msgctxt "an3.30:1.14"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, avakujjapañño puggalo. "
msgstr "This is called a person with upside-down wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.131, sc2
msgctxt "an3.30:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ucchaṅgapañño puggalo? "
msgstr "And who is the person with wisdom on their lap? "

