msgstr "While sitting there, that person pays attention to the discussion in the beginning, middle, and end. "

msgctxt "an3.30:2.12"
msgid "vuṭṭhito ca kho tamhā āsanā tassā kathāya neva ādiṃ manasi karoti, na majjhaṃ manasi karoti, na pariyosānaṃ manasi karoti. "
msgstr "But when they get up from their seat, they don’t pay attention to the beginning, middle, or end of the discussion. "

msgctxt "an3.30:2.13"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ucchaṅgapañño puggalo. "
msgstr "This is called a person with wisdom on their lap. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.30:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puthupañño puggalo? "
msgstr "And who is the person with wide wisdom? "

msgctxt "an3.30:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ārāmaṃ gantā hoti abhikkhaṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ santike dhammassavanāya. "
msgstr "It’s someone who often goes to the monastery to hear the teaching in the presence of the mendicants. "

msgctxt "an3.30:3.3"
msgid "Tassa bhikkhū dhammaṃ desenti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsenti. "
msgstr "The mendicants teach them Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And they reveal a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "an3.30:3.4"
msgid "So tasmiṃ āsane nisinno tassā kathāya ādimpi manasi karoti, majjhampi manasi karoti, pariyosānampi manasi karoti; "
msgstr "While sitting there, that person pays attention to the discussion in the beginning, middle, and end. "

msgctxt "an3.30:3.5"
msgid "vuṭṭhitopi tamhā āsanā tassā kathāya ādimpi manasi karoti, majjhampi manasi karoti, pariyosānampi manasi karoti. "
msgstr "And when they get up from their seat, they continue to pay attention to the beginning, middle, or end of the discussion. "

msgctxt "an3.30:3.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kumbho ukkujjo tatra udakaṃ āsittaṃ saṇṭhāti no vivaṭṭati; "
msgstr "It’s like when a pot full of water is set straight, so the water stays and doesn’t drain out. "

msgctxt "an3.30:3.7"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo ārāmaṃ gantā hoti abhikkhaṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ santike dhammassavanāya. "
msgstr "In the same way, someone often goes to the monastery to hear the teaching in the presence of the mendicants. "

msgctxt "an3.30:3.8"
msgid "Tassa bhikkhū dhammaṃ desenti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsenti. "
msgstr "The mendicants teach them Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And they reveal a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "an3.30:3.9"
msgid "So tasmiṃ āsane nisinno tassā kathāya ādimpi manasi karoti, majjhampi manasi karoti, pariyosānampi manasi karoti; "
msgstr "While sitting there, that person pays attention to the discussion in the beginning, middle, and end. "

msgctxt "an3.30:3.10"
msgid "vuṭṭhitopi tamhā āsanā tassā kathāya ādimpi manasi karoti, majjhampi manasi karoti, pariyosānampi manasi karoti. "
msgstr "And when they get up from their seat, they continue to pay attention to the beginning, middle, or end of the discussion. "

msgctxt "an3.30:3.11"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puthupañño puggalo. "
msgstr "This is called a person with wide wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.30:3.12"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasminti. "
msgstr "These are the three kinds of people found in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.30:4.1"
msgid "Avakujjapañño puriso, "
msgstr "A person with upside-down wisdom, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:4.2"
msgid "dummedho avicakkhaṇo; "
msgstr "is stupid and cannot see, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:4.3"
msgid "Abhikkhaṇampi ce hoti, "
msgstr "and even if they frequently "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:4.4"
msgid "gantā bhikkhūna santike. "
msgstr "go into the mendicants’ presence, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.30:5.1"
msgid "Ādiṃ kathāya majjhañca, "
msgstr "such a person can’t learn "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:5.2"
msgid "pariyosānañca tādiso; "
msgstr "the beginning, middle, or end "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:5.3"
msgid "Uggahetuṃ na sakkoti, "
msgstr "of the discussion, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:5.4"
msgid "paññā hissa na vijjati. "
msgstr "for their wisdom is lacking. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.30:6.1"
msgid "Ucchaṅgapañño puriso, "
msgstr "The person with wisdom on their lap "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:6.2"
msgid "seyyo etena vuccati; "
msgstr "is better than that, it’s said; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:6.3"
msgid "Abhikkhaṇampi ce hoti, "
msgstr "but even if they frequently "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:6.4"
msgid "gantā bhikkhūna santike. "
msgstr "go into the mendicants’ presence, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an3.30:7.1"
msgid "Ādiṃ kathāya majjhañca, "
msgstr "such a person can only learn "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:7.2"
msgid "pariyosānañca tādiso; "
msgstr "the beginning, middle, and end "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:7.3"
msgid "Nisinno āsane tasmiṃ, "
msgstr "while sitting in that seat; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:7.4"
msgid "uggahetvāna byañjanaṃ; "
msgstr "but they’ve only grasped the phrasing, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:7.5"
msgid "Vuṭṭhito nappajānāti, "
msgstr "for when they get up their understanding fails, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: gahitaṃ hissa → gahitampissa (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.30:7.6"
msgid "gahitaṃ hissa mussati. "
msgstr "and what they’ve learned is lost. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an3.30:8.1"
msgid "Puthupañño ca puriso, "
msgstr "The person with wide wisdom "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: etehi → etena (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an3.30:8.2"
msgid "seyyo etehi vuccati; "
msgstr "is better than that, it’s said; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:8.3"
msgid "Abhikkhaṇampi ce hoti, "
msgstr "and if they, too, frequently "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:8.4"
msgid "gantā bhikkhūna santike. "
msgstr "go into the mendicants’ presence, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.30:9.1"
msgid "Ādiṃ kathāya majjhañca, "
msgstr "such a person can learn "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:9.2"
msgid "pariyosānañca tādiso; "
msgstr "the beginning, middle, and end "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:9.3"
msgid "Nisinno āsane tasmiṃ, "
msgstr "while sitting in that seat; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:9.4"
msgid "uggahetvāna byañjanaṃ. "
msgstr "and when they’ve grasped the phrasing, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an3.30:10.1"
msgid "Dhāreti seṭṭhasaṅkappo, "
msgstr "they remember it with the best of intentions. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:10.2"
msgid "Abyaggamānaso naro; "
msgstr "That peaceful-hearted person, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:10.3"
msgid "Dhammānudhammappaṭipanno, "
msgstr "practicing in line with the teaching, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:10.4"
msgid "Dukkhassantakaro siyā”ti. "
msgstr "would make an end of suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.30:10.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.30:10.6"
msgid "Puggalavaggo tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc11
#. VAR: Samiddha → saviṭṭha (s1-3, km) | seṭṭha (mr)
msgctxt "an3.30:11.1"
msgid "Samiddha gilāna saṅkhārā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:11.2"
msgid "bahukārā vajirena ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:11.3"
msgid "Sevi jiguccha gūthabhāṇī, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.30:11.4"
msgid "andho ca avakujjatāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
